        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:12PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 412 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Walhalla, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Long Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
